The paper presents a new cognitive architecture for implementing emotions in computing systems, which involves the use of neuromodulators such as serotonin, dopamine, and noradrenaline. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Systems and Control (cs.SY), and Cybernetics (cs.CY).
